data.chText: 特殊的；特别的；不寻常的；不一般的
data.enText: not ordinary or usual; different from what is normal

data.chText: 学校只有在特殊情况下才会同意这种事。
data.enText: The school will only allow this in special circumstances.

data.chText: 有些官员享受特权。
data.enText: Some of the officials have special privileges.

data.chText: 这个地方有几分特别。
data.enText: There is something special about this place.

data.chText: 重要的；格外看重的；特别关照的
data.enText: more important than others; deserving or getting more attention than usual

data.chText: 你有哪些主要的爱好？
data.enText: What are your special interests?

data.chText: 她是我特别要好的朋友。
data.enText: She's a very special friend.

data.chText: 我们下周节目的特邀嘉宾是…
data.enText: Our special guest on next week's show will be…

data.chText: 别丢了——这可不是一般东西。
data.enText: Don't lose it ─ it's special.

data.chText: 特设的；有专门目的的；起专门作用的
data.enText: organized or intended for a particular purpose

data.chText: 特设活动
data.enText: a special event

data.chText: 这些教师需要专门的培训。
data.enText: These teachers need special training.

data.chText: 专用的；专门针对…的；特有的
data.enText: used by or intended for one particular person or group of people

data.chText: 她微笑的样子有些特别。
data.enText: She has a special way of smiling.

data.chText: 他给那些人专门去了一封信。
data.enText: He sent a special message to the men.

data.chText: 更好的；格外的
data.enText: better or more than usual

data.chText: 她是个独生女，所以备受关爱。
data.enText: As an only child she got special attention.

data.chText: 请对它多加关照。
data.enText: Please take special care of it.

data.chText: 特别活动（或节目等）；特制产品
data.enText: something that is not usually available but is provided for a particular purpose or on one occasion

data.chText: 选举之夜电视特别节目
data.enText: an election-night special on television

data.chText: 菜谱定期更换，而且每天都有特色菜供选择。
data.enText: The menu changes regularly and there are daily specials to choose from.

data.chText: 特价
data.enText: a price for a particular product in a shop/store or restaurant that is lower than usual

data.chText: 本周咖啡特价。
data.enText: There's a special on coffee this week.

simple_means.memory_skill: spec 外观；种类 + ial …的 →〔属于〕某种类 → 特别的

ex.chText: 酒吧里有一块专门用于聊天的地方。
ex.enText: There is a special place in the bar for chatting.

ex.chText: 她用特殊的方法做蛋挞。
ex.enText: She has a special recipe for egg tart.

ex.chText: 你们结婚15周年纪念有什么特别活动吗？
ex.enText: Are you doing anything special for your 15th wedding anniversary?

ex.chText: 处理此事我们需要你的特殊才能。
ex.enText: We need your special talents for handling this matter.

synonyms.bx: 普通用词，指事物在质量、特性、用途等方面不同于一般的，常含更重要或更好之意。

ex.chText: 我妹妹对蘑菇有着特殊的偏好。
ex.enText: My sister has an especial fondness for mushrooms.

ex.chText: 这是一件特别重要的事情。
ex.enText: This is a matter of especial importance.
He has an especial dislike for jazz music.

synonyms.bx: 和 special 基本同义，但更强调在程度上超出一般的，只作定语。

ex.chText: 你有什么特别的计划吗？
ex.enText: Do you have anything particular planned?
You should pay particular attention to grammar.

ex.chText: 她特别关心那名残疾儿童。
ex.enText: She showed particular concern for the disabled child.

synonyms.bx: 强调个性或特殊性，即侧重于个别的、特别的、不同于一般的情况、特点等。

ex.chText: 这幅画有一种独特的风格。
ex.enText: The picture has a specific style.

ex.chText: 这钱将用于某种特定用途。
ex.enText: The money is to be used for a specific purpose.

ex.chText: 他要一份对该问题的专门分析。
ex.enText: He wants a specific kind of analysis of the problem.

synonyms.bx: 指某一事物具有特定属性、风格等的，只作定语。

tr: a television production that features a particular person or work or topic
example: the last of a series of BBC specials on Iran is being shown tonight

tr: a special offering (usually temporary and at a reduced price) that is featured in advertising
example: they are having a special on pork chops

tr: a dish or meal given prominence in e.g. a restaurant
surpassing what is common or usual or expected
example: he paid especial attention to her
a matter of particular and unusual importance
a special reason to confide in her
what's so special about the year 2000?

tr: having a specific function or scope
example: a special (or specific) role in the mission

tr: for a special service or occasion
example: a special adviser to the committee
had to get special permission for the event
she gets special (or particular) satisfaction from her volunteer work

tr: adapted to or reserved for a particular purpose

example: put on special buses for the big game

value.def: Someone or something that is special is better or more important than other people or things.

example.ex: You're very special to me, darling...
example.tran: 亲爱的，你对我来说很重要。

example.ex: There are strong arguments for holidays at Easter and Christmas because these are special occasions...
example.tran: 支持复活节和圣诞节放假是有充分论据的，因为这些节日都是特殊的时刻。

example.ex: Just to see him was something special...
My special guest will be comedian Ben Elton.
example.tran: 我的特邀嘉宾将是喜剧演员本·艾尔顿。

example.ex: In special cases, a husband can deduct the travel expenses of his wife who accompanies him on a business trip...
example.tran: 在特殊情况下，丈夫可以扣除陪同出差的妻子的旅费。

example.ex: So you didn't notice anything special about him?...
example.tran: 这么说你并没有发现他有什么异常之处了？

example.ex: There is nothing worse than trying to relax and eat a special meal only to find clouds of cigarette smoke drifting over you.
example.tran: 本打算轻松一下，吃上一顿特别的饭菜，结果却发现周围烟雾缭绕——没有什么比这更糟糕了。

example.ex: ...'Little Scarlet' strawberry jam, made from a special variety of strawberry.
example.tran: 用特殊品种草莓制成的“小斯卡利特”牌草莓酱

value.def: You use special to describe someone who is officially appointed or who has a particular position specially created for them.

example.ex: Due to his wife's  illness, he returned to the State Department as special adviser to the President...
example.tran: 由于妻子生病，他回到了国务院，出任总统的特别顾问。

example.ex: Frank Deford is a special correspondent for Newsweek magazine.
example.tran: 弗兰克·德福特是《新闻周刊》杂志的特派记者。

value.def: Special institutions are for people who have serious physical or mental problems.

example.ex: Police are still searching for a convicted rapist, who escaped from Broadmoor special hospital yesterday.
example.tran: 警方仍然在搜寻昨天从布罗德莫尔专科医院逃跑的一名强奸犯。

value.tran: (为残疾人或有心理障碍者)特设的，专门的

value.def: You use special to describe something that relates to one particular person, group, or place.

example.ex: Every anxious person will have his or her own special problems or fears.
example.tran: 每一个焦虑的人都会有自己的问题或者担心。

example.ex: ...it requires a very special brand of courage to fight dictators.
example.tran: 与独裁者作斗争需要非同寻常的勇气。

value.def: A special is a product, programme, or meal which is not normally available, or which is made for a particular purpose.

example.tran: 对英国广播公司的万圣节特别节目《幽灵观察》的投诉

example.ex: Grocery stores have to offer enough specials to bring people into the store.
example.tran: 杂货店为了招揽顾客不得不推出多种特色产品。
脱口秀与新闻专题节目
